f(x)=\int_0^1|t-x|t~dt
x
f(x)
f(x)
x
t
x
f
x\ge 1
|t-x|=x-t
f(x) = \int_0^1t(x-t)dt = x/2-1/3
x\le 0
|t-x|=t-x
f(x)=\int_0^1t(t-x)dt = 1/3-x/2
x\in (0,1)
f(x)=\int_0^1t|t-x|dt =\int_0^xt|t-x|dt+\int_x^1t|t-x|dt  
=\int_0^xt(x-t)dt+\int_x^1t(t-x)dt = x^3/2-x^3/3+(1-x^3)/3-x(1-x^2)/2
=1/3-x/2+x^3/3. 
